devdoc.author: Civic Ledger

addTradingPeriod(bytes32,uint256,uint256.details: Adds a valid trading period for something identified by keyHash (can add multiple trading periods for a keyHash)

params.end: End date (expiry) of the trading period
params.keyHash: Key hash of the thing to be restricted
params.start: Start date of the trading period

canTrade(bytes32,uint256).details: Determines whether a party can trade based on their trading period

params.keyHash: Key hash of the thing being restricted

canTrade(bytes32,uint256).return: True if they have a valid trading period, false if they do not have a valid trading period

changeTradingPeriod(bytes32,uint256,uint.details: Updates a valid trading period with different start and end dates.

params.end: New end date (expiry) of the trading period
params.keyHash: Key hash of the thing to be restricted
params.periodIndex: Index of the trading period to change, as there can be multiple periods added
params.start: New start date of the trading period

tradingPeriodByKey(bytes32,uint256).details: Retrieves a trading period related to keyHash at period index

params.keyHash: Key hash of the thing being restricted
params.periodIndex: Index of the trading period to retrieve

tradingPeriodByKey(bytes32,uint256).return: Start date and end date of the trading period

tradingPeriodCountByKey(bytes32).details: Retrieves the count of trading periods related to keyHash, to support iteration

params.keyHash: Key hash of the thing being restricted

tradingPeriodCountByKey(bytes32).return: Count of trading period related to keyHash
